net.sf.click.jquery.taconite
Class JQCommand

java.lang.Object
  net.sf.click.jquery.taconite.JQCommand

public class JQCommand
extends Object

Provides the JQTaconite JQCommand class which is based on JQuery JQTaconite commands.

Commands map onto JQuery functions and consist of the following parts:

  • command - the command to execute, normally a JQuery function e.g: append, prepend, remove etc.
  • selector - a CSS selector to identify the target DOM elements.
  • content (optional) - a list of payloads for the command, usually one or more Click Controls but could be arbitrary HTML markup.
  • name (optional) - the name of an attribute
  • value (optional) - the value of an attribute
  • arguments (optional) - an array of arguments
For more documentation please refer to the JQuery JQTaconite commands section.

Creating custom commands

JQTaconite defines some predefined commands however you can easily define your own commands. For example if you want to execute the JQuery function text, you can formulate the following JQCommand: 
 public void onInit() {

     link.addBehavior(new AjaxBehavior()) {

         public ActionResult onAjaxAction(Control source) {
             JQTaconite actionResult = new JQTaconite();

             String commandName = "text";
             String selector = "#mySpan";
             String text = "Hello World";

             // Create the new command
             JQCommand command = new JQCommand(commandName, selector, text);

             // Add the command to JQTaconite
             actionResult.add(command);
             return actionResult;
         }
     }
 }
